    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Assert"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Assert` helps you **test** that your game logic actually does what you expect. Each method states something you believe is true — like \"the score should be 10\" — and reports whether it held up. Tests catch mistakes early, before players ever see them."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Asserts are used while building and testing. When your game runs normally for players, they're simply ignored — so they never slow anything down or show up in the finished game."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Comparing values"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "The most common check: confirm a value matches what you expect. Every assert takes a final **message** describing the check, which makes failures easy to read."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Passes when"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Equal(expected, actual, message)`", "`actual` equals `expected`."],
                ["`NotEqual(expected, actual, message)`", "The two values are different."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "int score = AddPoints(5, 5);",
                "Assert.Equal(10, score, \"adding 5 and 5 should give 10\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Checking conditions and values"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "Passes when"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`True(condition, message)`", "`condition` is `true`."],
                ["`False(condition, message)`", "`condition` is `false`."],
                ["`Null(value, message)`", "`value` is empty (null)."],
                ["`NotNull(value, message)`", "`value` is set (not null)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "Assert.True(player.health > 0, \"player should still be alive\");",
                "Assert.NotNull(savedGame, \"a saved game should have loaded\");"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Passing or failing on purpose"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Sometimes you want to declare a result directly — for example, fail a test if your code reaches a branch it never should."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Fail(message)`", "Marks the test as failed."],
                ["`Pass(testName)`", "Marks the test as passed."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "if (unexpectedState)",
                "{",
                "    Assert.Fail(\"we should never reach this state\");",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`Equal`", "`object expected, object actual, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`NotEqual`", "`object expected, object actual, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`True`", "`bool condition, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`False`", "`bool condition, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`Null`", "`object value, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`NotNull`", "`object value, string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`Fail`", "`string message`"],
                ["`void`", "`Pass`", "`string testName`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Write a clear `message` for every assert — when a test fails, that message is exactly what tells you what went wrong and where to look."
        }
    ]
}
